EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to local improvement projects; authorizing any
county, city or town to repair a private water or sewer
system that is owned by a common-interest community as
part of a neighborhood improvement project; and
providing other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law authorizes the governing body of any county, city or town to
2 create an improvement district for the acquisition, improvement, equipment,
3 operation and maintenance of certain local improvement projects, including a
4 neighborhood improvement project, and to finance the cost of any such project
5 through such methods as the issuance of certain bonds and the levy of assessments
6 upon property in the improvement district. (NRS 271.265, 271.270, 271.325)
7 Section 1 of this bill amends the definition of “neighborhood improvement project”
8 to include the improvement of a water or sewer system that is owned by a common-
9 interest community.
10 Existing law authorizes, under certain circumstances, the governing body of
11 any county, city or town to dissolve by resolution an improvement district that is
12 created for the purposes of a neighborhood improvement project. (NRS 271.296)
13 Section 2 of this bill provides that the authority to dissolve an improvement district
14 does not apply to a neighborhood improvement project that improves a water or
15 sewer system that is owned by a common-interest community.
16 Existing law sets forth certain notice requirements for a hearing as to the
17 propriety and advisability of an improvement project that has been provisionally
18 ordered by the governing body of a county, city or town. For a neighborhood
19 improvement project, the notice must state that: (1) a person who owns or resides
20 within a tract in the proposed improvement district may file a protest to inclusion in
